{
    "primary_issue": "The login form uses HTTP GET method, which exposes sensitive credentials (username and password) in the URL, query string, and browser history.",
    "evidence": "The form tag has method=\"get\", and the password field is named \"pass\". When submitted, credentials will be sent as URL parameters (e.g., /LoginServlet?name=user&pass=secret).",
    "fix_summary": "Change the form method from \"get\" to \"post\" to send credentials in the request body, preventing exposure in URLs, logs, and browser history."
}
